Published under the terms of the MIT License.

lw is a minimalistic log watch daemon written in pure C with no external
dependencies. It monitors changes in a configured set of log files and
runs other programs once any of configured patterns is found to be added
to a log file.


INSTALLATION

To install the daemon system-wide type

   make
   sudo make PREFIX=/usr install

The makefile also understands DESTDIR for a staged installation.


USAGE

Find details in the manual page (lw.8).
